The paper discusses closed-chain manipulation tasks using multi-arm robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves several developments, such as stabilizing the manipulated object using the environment (cs.AI), using a compliant control scheme (cs.SY), and flipping a chair frame (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves planning and control algorithms, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control theory (cs.SY).
